[SN]TITLE[SN]
Anthony Banting: Man charged over tram stop death

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Detectives investigating the death of a man at a tram stop in Birmingham have charged a man with murder.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Alaeldien Ahmed is accused of killing Anthony Banting, 57, of Sparkhill, Birmingham, at Soho Benson Road in the Winson Green area on 31 March.
The 26-year-old, of Eva Road, Winson Green, was arrested on Friday in connection with Mr Banting's death.
Father-of-four Mr Banting died from multiple stab wounds shortly after getting off a tram at 16:40 BST.
Mr Ahmed is due to appear before Birmingham Magistrates' Court on Monday.
